----PREREQUISITES----
*a) Install the MTi USB Serial Driver - follow the instructions below
git clone https://github.com/xsens/xsens_mt.git
cd ~/xsens_mt
make
sudo modprobe usbserial
sudo insmod ./xsens_mt.ko
*b) Install gps_common
sudo apt-get install ros-distro-gps-common
_____________________________________________________________________
----RUNNING XSENS MTi ROS NODE v1.0----
1. Copy the contents of the src folder into your catkin workspace 'src' folder. Change the permission to 'rw' using the chmod command for these folders
& folders. For details on creating a catkin workspace environment refer to "Creating a catkin ws" here
http://wiki.ros.org/ROS/Tutorials/InstallingandConfiguringROSEnvironment#Create_a_ROS_Workspace

2. in your catkin_ws folder, execute
catkin_make

3. source ~/catkin_ws/devel/setup.bash (Note: you have to do this for each terminal you open, if you are working in a single environment it is better to
source it automatically by editing your ~/.bashrc - add the line to end of the file)

4. Initiate 
roscore

5. Open a new terminal, type
rosrun xsens_driver mtdevice.py -q fs (fs can be 1,5,10,20,40,50,80,100,200 or 400Hz)
rosrun xsens_driver mtdevice.py -t fs (fs can be 1,5,10,20,40,50,80,100,200 or 400Hz)
e.g.
rosrun xsens_driver mtdevice.py -q 100 [this publishes the /xsens/sensorSample]
rosrun xsens_driver mtdevice.py -t 100 [this publishes the /imu/data]

This configures the MTi (MTi-10/20/30/100/200/300 or MTi-G-700) to output inertial data and magnetometer data at the set ODR. The maximum supported
inertial update rate is 400Hz and for the magnetometer it is 100Hz

6. To run the node
rosrun xsens_driver mtnode.py _device:=/dev/ttyUSB0 _baudrate:=115200
or
rosrun xsens_driver mtnode.py 

7. Open a new terminal (do not forget step 3)
rostopic echo /xsens/sensorSample  or rostopic echo /imu/data

